'''''Xanthophyllum bicolor''''' is a tree in the family [[Polygalaceae]]. The [[specific name (botany)|specific epithet]] ''{{lang|la|bicolor}}'' is from the [[Latin]] meaning "two-coloured", referring to the different colours of the leaf and [[Petiole (botany)|petiole]].<ref name=TFSS/>

==Description==
''Xanthophyllum bicolor'' grows up to {{convert|30|m|-1}} tall with a trunk diameter of up to {{convert|32|cm|-1}}. The bark is dark brown and smooth. The flowers are yellowish-orange, drying to brown-orange. The round fruits are blue turning light brown and measure up to {{convert|2|cm|in|0|abbr=on}} in diameter.<ref name=TFSS/>

==Distribution and habitat==
''Xanthophyllum bicolor'' is [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Borneo]]. Its habitat is mixed [[dipterocarp]] forests at low altitude.<ref name=TFSS/>

